Demonstrates per-station IEEE 802.11 data rate selection.

An access point transmits to each associated station at a different PHY data
rate, configured per receiver via the dataFrameBitratePerReceiver rate-selection
parameter. A wired server sends UDP downlink traffic through the access point to
three wireless stations, which the access point serves at 6, 24 and 54 Mbps.

Secondarily, the per-station rates can be watched live as a bar chart above the
access point: run in Qtenv (the Ieee80211RateVisualizer is enabled in the ini).
